Technomyrmex
Most easily confused with Paratrechina and Iridomyrmex, this genus is readily identified by the indentation or notch in its clypeal border and the presence of fine (but not stout) standing hairs. The two species of Technomyrmex in Micronesia can be distinguished by the lengths of their scapes, and if specimens of both species are obtained, relative body size and coloration.

