SUBFAMILY MYRMICINAE
TRIBE BASICEROTINI
Eurhopalothrix
Although closely related to the Dacetini (Pyramica and Stumigenys), this genus is much larger and has seven (instead of six) antennal segments in Micronesia. The odd male from Chuuk requires any collection of Basicerotini from the area to be carefully determined.
Eurhopalothrix procera (Emery 1897) Rhopalothrix procera Emery 1897
