Odontomachus
The one species of Odontomachus in Micronesia most closely resembles Anochetus, but O. simillimus is larger, darker, has a spine-like petiolar node, and has the ridge at the back of the head forming a V-shape at the vertex.
Odontomachus simillimus Smith, F. 1858
