Ponera
Recognizing the genus Ponera is difficult (see the first paragraph under Hypoponera above), and in most areas the species are equally challenging. Although my key relies on certain measurements and indices, the Ponera fauna of Micronesia is mercifully small and readily identified with well-mounted material and a good microscope.
Ponera clavicornis Emery 1900
Fig. 18
Specimens examined: FSM Pohnpei: Pohnpei I., Mt. Temwetemwensekir (summit, alt. ca. 1500 ft., dealate, Ad 50); Pohnpei I., S.E. Nanponmal (Exorrhiza stump B, Gr 51)
